entry.title: [Mac] Consider a frame audible when silent audio is playing
entry.content:
This is a temporary workaround for a priority inversion that happens

when the echo cancellation processing times out waiting for an audio

sample of a backgrounded renderer, which can happen when a renderer

is playing silent audio.



This is prevented with this change as renderers playing silent

audio will no longer get backgrounded.



Note that WebContents audibility (and the tab indicator) is not

impacted by this change. The audibility state of RenderFrameHostImpl

is used exclusively to control the priority of renderers.



This change is also no-op, as we currently do not enable renderer

backgrounding on MacOS yet.

entry.title: Lacros: Make InProcessBrowserTest wait for window creation
entry.content:
InProcessBrowserTest creates an initial browser. Tests should be able to

assume that this browser is visible. In Lacros tests that run

with Crosapi enabled, this requires extra work due to the concurrency of

Wayland and Crosapi.



- Add an explicit wait operation after the initial window

creation to avoid race conditions in tests. It also adds the same wait

operation to various methods for browser creation such as

CreateIncognitoBrowser.

The wait operation is a noop on any platform but Lacros.



- Simplify some existing tests that were manually doing wait operations

that are now redundant.



- Work around a race condition in InputMethodLacrosBrowserTest uncovered

by the change: Once the initial browser window is fully created, the

omnibox has focus. Some tests relied on focus being elsewhere

at the beginning of the test body.

entry.title: Fix the broken tests when AppStorage is enabled(Part 6).
entry.content:
When the kAppServiceStorage flag is enabled, AppService blocks the

app publishers creating until it's ready, after reading from the

AppStorage file. This affects some tests:



1. WebAppPublisherHelperTest.UpdateShortcutDoesPublishDelta

Since the web app publisher is created async, it replaces

NoOpWebAppPublisherDelegate, so the test reports error. Modify the test

to wait for AppServiceProxy to be ready, then create

NoOpWebAppPublisherDelegate.



2. WebAppDatabaseTest.*

The web app publisher is created async. When it is created, the init

process reports error, because hits the CHECK in

WebAppProvider::CheckIsConnected[1]. That is because

FakeWebAppProvider sets `connected_` as false via

CheckNotStartedAndDisconnect, when SetDatabaseFactory. So modify

the setup process to start the provider again after setting the sub

system to set `connected_` as true.



[1] https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:chrome/browser/web_applications/web_app_provider.cc?q=WebAppProvider::CheckIsConnected&ss=chromium%2Fchromium%2Fsrc

entry.title: MediaApp/A11y: Create a new mojo pipe for every new PDF document loaded.
entry.content:
Currently, a connection between the Media App and the a11y code running

OCR is established for each window. Switch to making a connection for

every document instead for a couple reasons:

- Loading a new document means all the information we already have from

OCR needs to be thrown out anyway, and

- This avoids having to overwrite / resize the internal AXTrees in the

A11y service on new document load, because instead everything is

being destroyed. This provides better security guarantees.



Also see the original suggestion in code review at

https://crrev.com/c/5016238/9.

entry.title: Pass attribution runtime features on fenced frame creation.
entry.content:
The AttributionReportingRuntimeFeatures are currently only available in

the renderer, and they need to be sent to the browser for attribution

reporting to work properly. Right now, they get passed during the call

to `setReportEventDataForAutomaticBeacons()`. Because automatic beacon

reporting is changing to allow beacons to send without setting any event

data, it will become a viable use case to have a fenced frame support

automatic beacon + attribution reporting without calling

`setReportEventDataForAutomaticBeacons()`.



This CL has the renderer pass AttributionReportingRuntimeFeatures when

the Fence object is created. Attribution runtime features are known at

frame creation time, so it is okay to pass this value earlier. This

information is stored in a new ARA-specific document user data subclass.



This change is already covered by the

ReportEventSameOriginSetsSupportHeader test in

fenced_frame_browsertest.cc, so no additional tests are required.

entry.title: [Extensions] Replace all uses of Feature::Context
entry.content:
Replace all uses of Feature::Context with mojom::ContextType. The

latter is a drop-in replacement for the former and is used in IPC

messaging (and also, is an enum class rather than an enum, yay!).



This is a mass-change to replace all instances with their direct

counterparts:

* Feature::BLESSED_EXTENSION_CONTEXT ->

mojom::ContextType::kPrivilegedExtension

* Feature::UNBLESSED_EXTENSION_CONTEXT ->

mojom::ContextType::kUnprivilegedExtension

* Feature::CONTENT_SCRIPT_CONTEXT ->

mojom::ContextType::kContentScript

* Feature::WEB_PAGE_CONTEXT -> mojom::ContextType::kWebPage

* Feature::BLESSED_WEB_PAGE_CONTEXT ->

mojom::ContextType::kPrivilegedWebPage

* Feature::WEBUI_CONTEXT -> mojom::ContextType::kWebUi

* Feature::WEBUI_UNTRUSTED_CONTEXT ->

mojom::ContextType::kUntrustedWebUi

* Feature::LOCK_SCREEN_EXTENSION_CONTEXT ->

mojom::ContextType::kLockscreenExtension

* Feature::OFFSCREEN_EXTENSION_CONTEXT ->

mojom::ContextType::kOffscreenExtension

* Feature::USER_SCRIPT_CONTEXT -> mojom::ContextType::kUserScript

* Feature::UNSPECIFIED_CONTEXT -> mojom::ContextType::kUnspecified



The only non-mechanical part of this CL is to remove

context_type_adapter.*, which previously converted between

Feature::Context and mojom::ContextType. This is no longer necessary,

since mojom::ContextType is now the only type.



This CL should have no effective behavior change.

entry.title: Add a perf_tests for a long French text
entry.content:
This patch adds `latin-ebook-french` perf_tests.



The Blink `perf_tests/layout` has line break/text layout for

English, Arabic, and Japanese.

* English uses an optimized code path for ASCII in

`LazyLineBreakIterator`, without using the ICU break

iterator.

* Arabic uses the ICU break iterator, but also includes the

BiDi algorithm.

* Japanese uses the ICU break iterator without the BiDi

algorithm, but almost every character has a break opportunity.



The French text has different characteristics from all these

languages, uses the ICU break iterator, without the BiDi

algorithm, and break opportunities are at word boundaries.



The text is a subset of "Du côté de chez Swann by Marcel

Proust" at the Project Gutenberg[1]. The same subset as the

one in the Speedometer3[2].



[1] https://gutenberg.org/ebooks/2650

[2] https://github.com/WebKit/Speedometer/blob/main/resources/editors/assets/longtext.html



Bug: 1503166
